{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-generic-show-tsx","path":"/learn/b1-english-for-developers/learn-common-phrasal-verbs-and-idioms/task-60","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"assignments":[],"bilibiliIds":null,"block":"learn-common-phrasal-verbs-and-idioms","challengeType":19,"description":"","nodules":null,"explanation":"<section id=\"explanation\">\n<p>Postoje dva uobičajena načina za kreiranje komparativnih pridjeva (comparatives). Izaberite vrstu u zavisnosti od broja slogova prideva.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Za <strong>pridev sa jednim slogom</strong>, dodajte <span class=\"highlighted-text\">-er</span> na kraju. Primer:</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">This explanation is much clearer than the other one.</span> – Kraj <span class=\"highlighted-text\">-er</span> se koristi zato što <span class=\"highlighted-text\">clear</span> je kratak pridev sa samo jednom slogom.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Za <strong>najduži pridev</strong> (2 ili više slogova), koristi <span class=\"highlighted-text\">more</span> + pridev. Primer:</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Ah, now the button looks more prominent. Users can't miss it.</span> – <span class=\"highlighted-text\">More</span> koristi se pre prideva zato što <span class=\"highlighted-text\">prominent</span> ima tri sloga i predugo je za vrstu <span class=\"highlighted-text\">-er</span>.</p>\n<p>Drugi primeri:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">This bedroom is smaller than ours at home.</span> – <span class=\"highlighted-text\">Small</span> je pridev sa jednom slogom, stoga se koristi tip/vrsta <span class=\"highlighted-text\">-er</span>, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">smaller</span>.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">I think cell phones are more useful than tablets.</span> – <span class=\"highlighted-text\">Useful</span> je pridev sa dve sloga, pa ne dodaje <span class=\"highlighted-text\">-er</span> na kraju, već prethodi sa <span cla